246
00:08:26,615 --> 00:08:27,674
We already finished them.

247
00:08:27,675 --> 00:08:29,815
I ate so many of them in this short time.

248
00:08:30,785 --> 00:08:32,445
- He ate a lot.
- Yes.

249
00:08:33,155 --> 00:08:35,185
- Where are we going today?
- Let's get going.

250
00:08:35,355 --> 00:08:38,184
Let's go and find the Whenever Guest of Bongcheon-dong.

251
00:08:38,185 --> 00:08:39,295
Okay.

252
00:08:40,455 --> 00:08:41,595
(Flinching)

253
00:08:42,495 --> 00:08:43,895
- It's getting longer.
- Right.

254
00:08:44,325 --> 00:08:46,265
The first Whenever Guest is Eom Yeon Hee.

255
00:08:46,435 --> 00:08:49,095
- "I've raised 40 kids so far."
- What?

256
00:08:50,035 --> 00:08:52,834
"I've been Seoul Mom to kids from all eight provinces..."

257
00:08:52,835 --> 00:08:55,034
- "for 37 years now."
- Who could she be?

258
00:08:55,035 --> 00:08:58,144
"My kitchen is filled with the pleasant chopping sounds..."

259
00:08:58,145 --> 00:08:59,714
"and the delicious aroma of stew."

260
00:08:59,715 --> 00:09:03,015
"Today, could you add a bowl of laughter to it?"

261
00:09:03,715 --> 00:09:05,444
"Kids from all eight provinces?"

262
00:09:05,445 --> 00:09:07,115
I got it. The students who live alone.

263
00:09:07,315 --> 00:09:08,684
- Wait. No, I meant...
- A boarding house.

264
00:09:08,685 --> 00:09:09,885
- A boarding house.
- My gosh.

265
00:09:10,025 --> 00:09:11,355
Or is she a chef?

266
00:09:12,755 --> 00:09:13,794
- "Pleasant..."
- You know?

267
00:09:13,795 --> 00:09:15,055
Is she a chef?

268
00:09:15,125 --> 00:09:16,365
- Or...
- Right.

269
00:09:16,495 --> 00:09:17,665
But she's Seoul Mom.

270
00:09:18,025 --> 00:09:19,994
- Seoul Mom.
- Seoul Mom.

271
00:09:19,995 --> 00:09:22,905
We failed to give presents both times last week, right?

272
00:09:23,465 --> 00:09:26,875
(They failed the mission both times in Daejeon last week.)

273
00:09:27,835 --> 00:09:30,175
We have to overcome this slump.

274
00:09:30,275 --> 00:09:31,945
Can you give us an easy one?

275
00:09:33,075 --> 00:09:34,175
Just this week.

276
00:09:34,645 --> 00:09:36,045
Are you good at games?

277
00:09:36,145 --> 00:09:37,984
Well, I wouldn't say I'm bad at them.

278
00:09:37,985 --> 00:09:40,114
- But I'll have to play to know.
- I especially...

279
00:09:40,115 --> 00:09:41,985
You get nervous easily during games, right?

280
00:09:42,115 --> 00:09:43,585
I don't get nervous during games.

281
00:09:43,685 --> 00:09:45,225
- Really?
- Right. That's great.

282
00:09:45,455 --> 00:09:46,824
He doesn't get nervous.

283
00:09:46,825 --> 00:09:48,025
Sure. I can do everything.

284
00:09:48,525 --> 00:09:50,665
It will be nice... I mean, I'll crush them.

285
00:09:52,025 --> 00:09:53,234
(Declaring in the frailest voice)

286
00:09:53,235 --> 00:09:54,595
- This is what he's like.
- I see.

287
00:09:54,895 --> 00:09:56,065
He's interesting.

288
00:09:56,665 --> 00:09:58,735
- Let me look it up.
- Yes, look up the address.

289
00:09:59,475 --> 00:10:00,675
The distance...

290
00:10:01,405 --> 00:10:03,704
- How long will it take on foot?
- It's 23 minutes away.

291
00:10:03,705 --> 00:10:05,505
(It will take 23 minutes on foot.)

292
00:10:06,315 --> 00:10:07,715
Let's take a taxi today.

293
00:10:07,775 --> 00:10:09,935
- Let's do that. It's freezing.
- It's freezing today.

294
00:10:10,045 --> 00:10:11,514
- We can go down.
- Shall we go?

295
00:10:11,515 --> 00:10:12,714
- Yes.
- The driver is two minutes away.

296
00:10:12,715 --> 00:10:13,715
Let's wait downstairs.

297
00:10:13,716 --> 00:10:14,891
We're lucky. We're taking a taxi.

298
00:10:14,915 --> 00:10:16,955
- Right.
- We were worried we'd be too cold.

299
00:10:17,185 --> 00:10:18,624
- He's all bones.
- Do you get cold easily?

300
00:10:18,625 --> 00:10:19,825
He's all bones.

301
00:10:19,955 --> 00:10:22,154
I'm good. But she keeps saying I get cold easily.

302
00:10:22,155 --> 00:10:23,325
But you do.

303
00:10:23,895 --> 00:10:25,871
- If it gets really cold...
- He gets cold so easily.

304
00:10:25,895 --> 00:10:27,571
Gosh, you make me want to take care of you.

305
00:10:27,595 --> 00:10:29,195
(Laughing)

306
00:10:29,965 --> 00:10:31,065
Is that the taxi?

307
00:10:31,505 --> 00:10:33,135
By the way... It's here.

308
00:10:33,905 --> 00:10:35,634
- You can sit in the front.
- We'll get in first.

309
00:10:35,635 --> 00:10:37,544
- We'll sit in the back.
- No, we'll sit in the back.

310
00:10:37,545 --> 00:10:39,004
- But still...
- I'll sit in the back.

311
00:10:39,005 --> 00:10:40,614
- Hello.
- You're our guests.

312
00:10:40,615 --> 00:10:42,145
- You should sit in the front.
- Okay.

313
00:10:42,515 --> 00:10:44,884
- My goodness.
- Hello.

314
00:10:44,885 --> 00:10:46,584
- Hello.
- My gosh.

315
00:10:46,585 --> 00:10:47,854
(They all get in the taxi together.)

316
00:10:47,855 --> 00:10:50,654
Yeon Shik always calls taxis...

317
00:10:50,655 --> 00:10:51,955
and guides us there.

318
00:10:52,385 --> 00:10:54,494
- I wanted us to be there on time.
- Exactly.

319
00:10:54,495 --> 00:10:55,895
- We must be punctual.
- Yes.

320
00:10:56,025 --> 00:10:57,124
We only have ten minutes left.

321
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:58,164
(Looking around)

322
00:10:58,165 --> 00:10:59,195
Right.

323
00:10:59,465 --> 00:11:01,695
By the way, it has the same vibe...

324
00:11:02,035 --> 00:11:03,534
from all those years ago.

325
00:11:03,535 --> 00:11:04,704
- Really? The vibe here?
- The vibe. Yes.

326
00:11:04,705 --> 00:11:06,575
- You lived around here?
- Yes, that's right.

327
00:11:07,405 --> 00:11:10,845
My friends used to live here, so we explored this area a lot.

328
00:11:11,175 --> 00:11:13,844
I had a go-to spot when I lived here.

329
00:11:13,845 --> 00:11:15,721
I used to walk to Seoul National University Station.

330
00:11:15,745 --> 00:11:17,385
Raboum Outlet was there.

331
00:11:17,785 --> 00:11:20,314
- I went there almost every day.
- You did?

332
00:11:20,315 --> 00:11:21,815
There was a karaoke room.

333
00:11:23,555 --> 00:11:25,885
I went there at least four times a week.

334
00:11:26,755 --> 00:11:28,194
- You went there so often.
- I was there every day.

335
00:11:28,195 --> 00:11:29,224
I befriended the owner.

336
00:11:29,225 --> 00:11:31,525
- I used to spend my time there.
- Right.

337
00:11:31,595 --> 00:11:33,135
I wonder if she's doing well.

338
00:11:35,835 --> 00:11:36,865
Seriously.

339
00:11:37,305 --> 00:11:41,134
Then we should ask Sun Bin to pick a restaurant for lunch.

340
00:11:41,135 --> 00:11:42,505
- That sounds good.
- And...

341
00:11:43,645 --> 00:11:44,975
I wonder if they're still here.

342
00:11:45,375 --> 00:11:47,144
What do you want to eat, Young Dae?

343
00:11:47,145 --> 00:11:48,275
Spicy stir-fried pork.

344
00:11:48,775 --> 00:11:50,284
- Do you like spicy stir-fried pork?
- That sounds good.

345
00:11:50,285 --> 00:11:51,514
A lot of people say...

346
00:11:51,515 --> 00:11:52,684
- that's comfort food for men.
- That sounds good.

347
00:11:52,685 --> 00:11:54,484
Spicy stir-fried pork is especially good...

348
00:11:54,485 --> 00:11:56,254
- when you mix it with rice.
- It just calls for more rice.

349
00:11:56,255 --> 00:11:58,125
- It calls for rice.
- Totally.

350
00:11:59,085 --> 00:12:01,024
There must be many good restaurants for spicy stir-fried pork here.

351
00:12:01,025 --> 00:12:02,594
- I know what you're thinking.
- Like diners taxi drivers frequent.

352
00:12:02,595 --> 00:12:04,564
- Hidden restaurants.
- Right? A rice meal.

353
00:12:04,565 --> 00:12:05,565
A rice meal restaurant.

354
00:12:05,895 --> 00:12:07,035
That sounds good.

355
00:12:07,795 --> 00:12:10,764
Sun Bin is happy to do anything Young Dae wants.

356
00:12:10,765 --> 00:12:12,735
- Of course.
- Right.

357
00:12:13,605 --> 00:12:16,045
- We're here. It's here.
- This is the place?

358
00:12:17,645 --> 00:12:18,774
- This is the place?
- Yes.

359
00:12:18,775 --> 00:12:21,074
It's one of the houses on our right.

360
00:12:21,075 --> 00:12:22,075
- On our right?
- Shall we?

361
00:12:22,076 --> 00:12:23,215
Yes.

362
00:12:23,345 --> 00:12:24,415
Thank you.

363
00:12:24,685 --> 00:12:26,254
- Have a good day.
- Thank you.

364
00:12:26,255 --> 00:12:28,754
- Thank you.
- Thank you. Happy New Year.

365
00:12:28,755 --> 00:12:29,825
Wait.

366
00:12:30,755 --> 00:12:32,955
- It looks like a boarding house.
- Exactly.

367
00:12:33,095 --> 00:12:34,425
- It has to be.
- Hold on.

368
00:12:34,595 --> 00:12:35,924
The house number is 22.

369
00:12:35,925 --> 00:12:37,895
- It's...
- The house number is 22?

370
00:12:38,625 --> 00:12:40,135
That one is 23.

371
00:12:40,335 --> 00:12:41,894
Then is that 22?

372
00:12:41,895 --> 00:12:43,205
This house... It's 26.

373
00:12:43,405 --> 00:12:45,364
- It's 23.
- That's 20. Over there, it's 21.

374
00:12:45,365 --> 00:12:46,475
This is...

375
00:12:46,575 --> 00:12:48,304
(Looking around)

376
00:12:48,305 --> 00:12:49,674
Is it down there? It's 22!

377
00:12:49,675 --> 00:12:50,874
- I found it. It's 22.
- Where?

378
00:12:50,875 --> 00:12:51,905
- Right here.
- Where?

379
00:12:52,845 --> 00:12:54,014
- Twenty-two.
- You startled me.

380
00:12:54,015 --> 00:12:55,335
- This is the house.
- Young Dae.

381
00:12:55,515 --> 00:12:56,744
You scared me.

382
00:12:56,745 --> 00:12:58,215
It's on the second floor.

383
00:12:58,585 --> 00:13:00,214
- Where?
- The house number is 22.

384
00:13:00,215 --> 00:13:01,914
- So the 2nd floor...
- The 2nd floor of this building?

385
00:13:01,915 --> 00:13:03,024
- Yes.
- I guess we were right.

386
00:13:03,025 --> 00:13:04,054
- It must be a boarding house.
- Wait. This is...

387
00:13:04,055 --> 00:13:05,284
It looks like a boarding house, right?

388
00:13:05,285 --> 00:13:06,845
- Look on the right.
- It says it here.

389
00:13:07,225 --> 00:13:08,894
- "Madam Eom's Boarding House."
- A boarding house.

390
00:13:08,895 --> 00:13:11,164
- Eom Yeon Hee is her name.
- Wait.

391
00:13:11,165 --> 00:13:12,894
- "Real Jipbap."
- It's a boarding house.

392
00:13:12,895 --> 00:13:14,541
- As in real home-cooked meals.
- I see. A boarding house.

393
00:13:14,565 --> 00:13:15,864
Hold on. This house... We should...

394
00:13:15,865 --> 00:13:17,534
- Should we press this?
- The second floor...

395
00:13:17,535 --> 00:13:18,765
Is that for the second floor?

396
00:13:21,575 --> 00:13:24,304
- Who is it?
- Is this Ms. Eom's house?

397
00:13:24,305 --> 00:13:27,214
- Yes. It is.
- Could you let us in?

398
00:13:27,215 --> 00:13:28,245
Sure.

399
00:13:28,715 --> 00:13:31,144
It must be a boarding house. She's coming down.

400
00:13:31,145 --> 00:13:32,585
(Intrigued)

401
00:13:32,745 --> 00:13:33,785
My gosh.

402
00:13:34,715 --> 00:13:36,015
- Hello.
- Hello.

403
00:13:39,695 --> 00:13:42,555
- Gosh, hello.
- Hello. Are you Yeon Hee?

404
00:13:42,895 --> 00:13:44,894
- Yes.
- Let's go upstairs.

405
00:13:44,895 --> 00:13:47,735
- Okay. Thank you for coming.
- Gosh, no.

406
00:13:48,065 --> 00:13:51,565
- This is a boarding house.
- That's right.

407
00:13:51,805 --> 00:13:53,605
- All right.
- Yes.

408
00:13:55,375 --> 00:13:56,644
I've never been to a boarding house.

409
00:13:56,645 --> 00:13:58,205
- Really?
- Yes.

410
00:13:58,775 --> 00:14:00,315
- I wanted to live in one.
- This...

411
00:14:00,515 --> 00:14:01,515
(Excited to visit a boarding house)

412
00:14:01,516 --> 00:14:02,984
- This is... Hello.
- Come on in.

413
00:14:02,985 --> 00:14:04,684
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

414
00:14:04,685 --> 00:14:06,085
- Gosh, you have...
- Hello.

415
00:14:06,385 --> 00:14:07,891
- You're so beautiful.
- You have a lovely house.

416
00:14:07,915 --> 00:14:12,125
Ms. Eom did a great job decorating the house.

417
00:14:12,785 --> 00:14:14,695
- I see. I agree.
- Welcome.

418
00:14:15,395 --> 00:14:17,924
- Hello.
- Gosh, you're all good-looking.

419
00:14:17,925 --> 00:14:18,965
My gosh.

420
00:14:19,565 --> 00:14:21,335
- Let's sit down.
- Please sit.

421
00:14:21,435 --> 00:14:22,664
- You can sit over there.
- Sure.

422
00:14:22,665 --> 00:14:23,765
Should I go to that side?

423
00:14:24,035 --> 00:14:26,505
- This feels like a real home.
- Having guests...

424
00:14:26,635 --> 00:14:27,635
You've never been to a boarding house?

425
00:14:27,636 --> 00:14:29,434
No. I always had this fantasy...

426
00:14:29,435 --> 00:14:31,104
- about boarding houses.
- You had a fantasy.

427
00:14:31,105 --> 00:14:32,244
- I see.
- Yes.

428
00:14:32,245 --> 00:14:34,575
When I was growing up, boarding houses were prevalent.

429
00:14:34,675 --> 00:14:37,021
- Right. There were so many of them.
- There was a ton of them.

430
00:14:37,045 --> 00:14:38,884
Boarding houses were everywhere...

431
00:14:38,885 --> 00:14:40,685
- in the 80s and 90s.
- Right.

432
00:14:40,985 --> 00:14:43,224
- People live in studios now.
- Right, in the studios.

433
00:14:43,225 --> 00:14:45,154
- They live alone now.
- There are many studios.

434
00:14:45,155 --> 00:14:46,155
- Right?
- There are so many of them.

435
00:14:46,156 --> 00:14:48,154
You wrote in your letter you've been running the house...

436
00:14:48,155 --> 00:14:50,865
- for 37 years now.
- Yes.

437
00:14:51,025 --> 00:14:53,535
My mother used to run it, but I took it over.

438
00:14:54,495 --> 00:14:56,305
My mother-in-law used to run the house.

439
00:14:56,435 --> 00:14:58,134
I got married in 1988.

440
00:14:58,135 --> 00:15:00,035
She was already running the house by then.

441
00:15:00,335 --> 00:15:01,705
I learned how to run it.

442
00:15:01,835 --> 00:15:04,604
It's been about 26 years since I took over.

443
00:15:04,605 --> 00:15:05,975
- It's been a long time.
- Oh, my.

444
00:15:06,275 --> 00:15:08,074
How many boarders do you have now?

445
00:15:08,075 --> 00:15:11,085
I have six boarders now.

446
00:15:11,315 --> 00:15:12,955
- That's a lot.
- That's a lot of people.

447
00:15:14,255 --> 00:15:17,285
(Countless boarders have passed through this house.)

448
00:15:18,655 --> 00:15:21,125
(Ms. Eom and her family live on the 2nd floor.)

449
00:15:22,555 --> 00:15:24,755
(She cooks for the boarders every morning and evening.)

450
00:15:27,935 --> 00:15:32,005
(They all gather here and have meals together.)

451
00:15:33,535 --> 00:15:36,875
(They share their meals over friendly conversations.)

452
00:15:37,005 --> 00:15:40,545
(And it gives off the vibe of a boarding house from years ago.)

453
00:15:42,075 --> 00:15:43,944
(On a floor higher...)

454
00:15:43,945 --> 00:15:47,015
Back in the day, 2 people used to share 1 room.

455
00:15:47,285 --> 00:15:48,814
Now, they don't share rooms.

456
00:15:48,815 --> 00:15:50,485
They have their own room.

457
00:15:50,985 --> 00:15:54,694
I reckon that students these days must be different...

458
00:15:54,695 --> 00:15:56,665
from students from years ago.

459
00:15:56,695 --> 00:16:00,495
Back then, all of my boarders were Seoul National University students.

460
00:16:00,665 --> 00:16:01,945
- They all went to SNU.
- I see.

461
00:16:02,065 --> 00:16:04,365
But those SNU students didn't study here.

462
00:16:04,635 --> 00:16:05,664
Really?

463
00:16:05,665 --> 00:16:07,204
They mostly ate and hung out.

464
00:16:07,205 --> 00:16:08,805
- They were romantic in a way.
- Really?

465
00:16:09,105 --> 00:16:10,574
- They were romantic.
- Yes.

466
00:16:10,575 --> 00:16:13,275
People used to call it the romance on campus.

467
00:16:13,375 --> 00:16:16,015
- There was romance in their lives.
- Right.

468
00:16:16,515 --> 00:16:20,015
Living in my boarding house used to offer a unique sense of romance too.

469
00:16:20,985 --> 00:16:22,254
We went on orientation trips...

470
00:16:22,255 --> 00:16:23,575
- Really?
- in summer and winter.

471
00:16:23,755 --> 00:16:25,955
- With boarders?
- It'd be over ten students.

472
00:16:26,125 --> 00:16:27,195
We went twice a week.

473
00:16:27,595 --> 00:16:30,495
We used to go on trips every summer and winter.

474
00:16:31,465 --> 00:16:34,965
Back then, my husband had flexibility with his work schedule.

475
00:16:36,095 --> 00:16:39,465
When the drama series, "Reply 1988," aired, students from those days...

476
00:16:39,935 --> 00:16:41,835
called me.

477
00:16:42,175 --> 00:16:44,244
- After watching the drama.
- "It brings back old memories."

478
00:16:44,245 --> 00:16:46,044
They said, "The drama reminded me of the old days."

479
00:16:46,045 --> 00:16:47,875
- They called me.
- Of course.

480
00:16:48,115 --> 00:16:50,544
But now, you can't even think about going on those trips.

481
00:16:50,545 --> 00:16:51,584
Right.

482
00:16:51,585 --> 00:16:53,145
(A kind of romance hard to imagine now)

483
00:16:54,015 --> 00:16:56,215
- Do you always have them here?
- No.

484
00:16:56,425 --> 00:16:57,485
They're for us, right?

485
00:16:57,625 --> 00:16:59,384
Two of my boarders are...

486
00:16:59,385 --> 00:17:01,625
- from Jeju Island.
- My gosh.

487
00:17:01,795 --> 00:17:04,664
- We have tangerines in winter.
- Their parents always send these.

488
00:17:04,665 --> 00:17:06,895
- They always send us tangerines.
- Oh, my.

489
00:17:07,065 --> 00:17:08,134
I keep the boxes on the steps,

490
00:17:08,135 --> 00:17:10,404
so they can freely grab some after their meal.

491
00:17:10,405 --> 00:17:12,365
- For desserts.
- So they can eat the tangerines.

492
00:17:12,405 --> 00:17:14,085
- Let's try some tangerines.
- Tangerines.

493
00:17:14,205 --> 00:17:15,834
- Tangerines from Jeju Island.
