To think I'd ride it...

1237
00:42:43,228 --> 00:42:45,098
- with Yoo Jae Suk.
- With Jae Suk.

1238
00:42:46,428 --> 00:42:47,527
With Jae Suk.

1239
00:42:47,528 --> 00:42:48,568
(Everything is still new.)

1240
00:42:48,738 --> 00:42:50,337
Really, what an experience.

1241
00:42:50,338 --> 00:42:51,468
- Right?
- Yes.

1242
00:42:52,368 --> 00:42:55,837
Did they ever succeed Round Three on both spare times?

1243
00:42:55,838 --> 00:42:57,878
I'm not sure.

1244
00:42:58,648 --> 00:43:01,247
Was there a time they succeeded both spare times?

1245
00:43:01,248 --> 00:43:02,947
- Yes.
- Until Round Three?

1246
00:43:02,948 --> 00:43:04,548
(So there was.)

1247
00:43:05,018 --> 00:43:07,348
- I want to beat it.
- Why do I want to succeed so badly?

1248
00:43:07,618 --> 00:43:08,817
- "The Fiery Priest."
- With "The Fiery Priest."

1249
00:43:08,818 --> 00:43:10,487
(Whenever Friends didn't fail.)

1250
00:43:10,488 --> 00:43:11,557
Han Ji Min and Lee Jun Hyuk.

1251
00:43:11,558 --> 00:43:13,134
(Teams "The Fiery Priest" and "Love Scout")

1252
00:43:13,158 --> 00:43:14,488
- We must beat them.
- Of course.

1253
00:43:14,828 --> 00:43:16,058
Stay focused.

1254
00:43:17,158 --> 00:43:19,868
(While the two are burning with passion)

1255
00:43:20,298 --> 00:43:23,698
You saw that, right? How I overcame my nervousness.

1256
00:43:23,968 --> 00:43:26,707
Don't you remember dropping the bowl? That was ridiculous.

1257
00:43:26,708 --> 00:43:29,778
Come on. It could happen, no?

1258
00:43:30,578 --> 00:43:31,848
I was dumbfounded.

1259
00:43:32,208 --> 00:43:34,548
- How come? It could totally happen.
- For real.

1260
00:43:35,978 --> 00:43:37,818
You make mistakes in life, don't you?

1261
00:43:39,088 --> 00:43:40,648
But you always make mistakes.

1262
00:43:40,888 --> 00:43:43,287
- We succeeded.
- You do whenever we play games.

1263
00:43:43,288 --> 00:43:44,788
- Either way, we succeeded.
- Gosh.

1264
00:43:44,988 --> 00:43:46,127
Search must-eat places...

1265
00:43:46,128 --> 00:43:47,758
- in Nakseongdae.
- Okay.

1266
00:43:48,098 --> 00:43:49,934
We have to get off the bus near Nakseongdae Entrance.

1267
00:43:49,958 --> 00:43:51,097
- Okay.
- There's a lot...

1268
00:43:51,098 --> 00:43:52,138
near Nakseongdae Entrance.

1269
00:43:52,798 --> 00:43:54,867
Near Nakseongdae Entrance...

1270
00:43:54,868 --> 00:43:56,198
(Searching must-eat places)

1271
00:43:56,368 --> 00:43:57,468
Sundae gukbap.

1272
00:43:58,368 --> 00:44:00,938
- I'm fine with anything.
- "Astounding Wang-sundae."

1273
00:44:01,308 --> 00:44:03,268
- This place is famous.
- Everything sounds good.

1274
00:44:03,708 --> 00:44:04,738
Okay.

1275
00:44:05,608 --> 00:44:07,507
Astounding Wang-sundae is really good.

1276
00:44:07,508 --> 00:44:09,418
- Is it?
- Is it that good?

1277
00:44:10,048 --> 00:44:11,147
- Is it the best?
- Yes.

1278
00:44:11,148 --> 00:44:12,518
- Have you tried the place?
- Yes.

1279
00:44:12,848 --> 00:44:13,947
Is Astounding Wang-sundae the best?

1280
00:44:13,948 --> 00:44:15,358
Are you an SNU student?

1281
00:44:15,758 --> 00:44:17,957
- No wonder. I knew it.
- Gosh.

1282
00:44:17,958 --> 00:44:19,788
If it's recommended by an SNU student...

1283
00:44:20,328 --> 00:44:22,398
You must be really happy to attend SNU.

1284
00:44:22,658 --> 00:44:24,528
May I ask what you're majoring in?

1285
00:44:25,468 --> 00:44:26,927
- Business.
- Business?

1286
00:44:26,928 --> 00:44:28,097
(Impressed)

1287
00:44:28,098 --> 00:44:30,697
- She'll become a CEO in the future.
- Exactly.

1288
00:44:30,698 --> 00:44:32,708
Just you wait. She'll be on the news.

1289
00:44:33,568 --> 00:44:35,678
(Glancing)

1290
00:44:35,778 --> 00:44:37,618
- She says it's good.
- This girl attends SNU.

1291
00:44:37,678 --> 00:44:40,348
- We didn't ask, but she heard us...
- Yes.

1292
00:44:40,408 --> 00:44:42,417
And told us Astounding Wang-sundae was good.

1293
00:44:42,418 --> 00:44:43,648
The place must be famous.

1294
00:44:46,218 --> 00:44:48,288
- Sundae gukbap in winter.
- It sounds good.

1295
00:44:49,618 --> 00:44:50,858
Look, students.

1296
00:44:51,788 --> 00:44:52,927
They're wearing school uniforms.

1297
00:44:52,928 --> 00:44:55,027
(A bunch of students in uniforms get on.)

1298
00:44:55,028 --> 00:44:58,467
The students have no idea Yoo Jae Suk is sitting...

1299
00:44:58,468 --> 00:45:00,728
- at the back, right?
- Not at the moment.

1300
00:45:02,738 --> 00:45:04,038
- But we do.
- Yes.

1301
00:45:04,568 --> 00:45:06,108
I so want to tell them.

1302
00:45:08,378 --> 00:45:10,377
"Yoo Jae Suk is in this very bus!"

1303
00:45:10,378 --> 00:45:12,078
("Yoo Jae Suk is in this very bus!")

1304
00:45:12,948 --> 00:45:14,777
Let's get off at the upcoming station.

1305
00:45:14,778 --> 00:45:15,918
- Here?
- Yes.

1306
00:45:17,948 --> 00:45:19,748
- Thank you.
- Gosh.

1307
00:45:20,988 --> 00:45:22,618
- Hold on.
- This way.

1308
00:45:22,818 --> 00:45:24,487
- Korean boxed lunch.
- Where's Amusing Wang-sundae?

1309
00:45:24,488 --> 00:45:26,928
It's "Astounding," not "Amusing."

1310
00:45:27,158 --> 00:45:28,457
It's not "Amusing."

1311
00:45:28,458 --> 00:45:29,957
(Heading straight to Something Wang-sundae)

1312
00:45:29,958 --> 00:45:31,257
- We...
- Turn right.

1313
00:45:31,258 --> 00:45:33,367
- The student majoring in biz...
- Yes.

1314
00:45:33,368 --> 00:45:34,997
- In business.
- Yes, business.

1315
00:45:34,998 --> 00:45:36,267
The place...

1316
00:45:36,268 --> 00:45:37,828
- highly recommended by her.
- Exactly.

1317
00:45:38,568 --> 00:45:40,437
We need a hearty meal to succeed in the next game.

1318
00:45:40,438 --> 00:45:41,678
We must fuel up.

1319
00:45:42,508 --> 00:45:43,538
It's over there, Jae Suk.

1320
00:45:44,108 --> 00:45:45,807
- Where?
- The sundae place.

1321
00:45:45,808 --> 00:45:47,077
- Over there?
- Yes.

1322
00:45:47,078 --> 00:45:49,177
- Hi.
- Welcome.

1323
00:45:49,178 --> 00:45:50,978
- Let's sit over here.
- Hi.

1324
00:45:51,278 --> 00:45:54,488
Jae Suk, how about one suyuk?

1325
00:45:54,958 --> 00:45:56,217
- We'd like to order.
- Sure.

1326
00:45:56,218 --> 00:45:58,928
- Four sundae gukbap and one suyuk.
- Okay.

1327
00:45:59,388 --> 00:46:02,328
And sundae? One large sundae.

1328
00:46:03,098 --> 00:46:04,158
I can't wait to eat it.

1329
00:46:04,628 --> 00:46:06,298
Highly recommended by the student...

1330
00:46:07,328 --> 00:46:08,438
We've got to try it.

1331
00:46:08,798 --> 00:46:10,267
We didn't even ask.

1332
00:46:10,268 --> 00:46:11,397
(She voluntarily recommended it.)

1333
00:46:11,398 --> 00:46:12,867
She just said it after hearing us.

1334
00:46:12,868 --> 00:46:14,444
Because we were talking about sundae soup.

1335
00:46:14,468 --> 00:46:16,378
- Thank you.
- Enjoy your food.

1336
00:46:16,838 --> 00:46:19,007
Look at the size of that thing. It certainly is large.

1337
00:46:19,008 --> 00:46:20,148
(Resilient and moist sundae)

1338
00:46:21,048 --> 00:46:24,277
Pork head meat. We passed Round Three,

1339
00:46:24,278 --> 00:46:26,117
- Right.
- so let's enjoy it.

1340
00:46:26,118 --> 00:46:28,148
(Let's enjoy our food now that we succeeded.)

1341
00:46:28,588 --> 00:46:29,657
(Their rice bowls are here.)

1342
00:46:29,658 --> 00:46:31,988
- Thank you.
- The rice bowls remind me of...

1343
00:46:32,328 --> 00:46:34,427
- One for each.
- Can we get two more?

1344
00:46:34,428 --> 00:46:36,358
- Sure.
- This reminds me.

1345
00:46:36,928 --> 00:46:38,497
It makes me want to flip it.

1346
00:46:38,498 --> 00:46:39,697
(The urge to flip it)

1347
00:46:39,698 --> 00:46:41,567
- Gosh.
- Try it.

1348
00:46:41,568 --> 00:46:42,808
- Shall we?
- It must be tasty.

1349
00:46:43,168 --> 00:46:44,267
Let's try the sundae.

1350
00:46:44,268 --> 00:46:47,238
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

1351
00:46:47,438 --> 00:46:49,138
(Trying the large sundae first)

1352
00:46:49,938 --> 00:46:51,378
- The salted shrimp too.
- Okay.

1353
00:46:52,878 --> 00:46:55,077
(Moaning)

1354
00:46:55,078 --> 00:46:56,377
Go ahead.

1355
00:46:56,378 --> 00:46:59,247
(Yeon Seok and Sun Bin try it with salted shrimp.)

1356
00:46:59,248 --> 00:47:01,148
(Eating)

1357
00:47:02,588 --> 00:47:03,688
It's so tender.

1358
00:47:06,188 --> 00:47:07,427
(Surprised)

1359
00:47:07,428 --> 00:47:08,598
It's good.

1360
00:47:08,698 --> 00:47:10,858
- I see why she recommended it.
- Yes.

1361
00:47:11,728 --> 00:47:13,767
- Here's your soup. Be careful.
- Thank you.

1362
00:47:13,768 --> 00:47:14,928
Thank you.

1363
00:47:15,668 --> 00:47:17,937
- It looks scrumptious.
- Yes.

1364
00:47:17,938 --> 00:47:18,938
(Hot and spicy sundae soup)

1365
00:47:18,939 --> 00:47:21,238
- It looks nice and spicy.
- Yes.

1366
00:47:22,678 --> 00:47:23,958
Look at the size of this sundae.

1367
00:47:25,708 --> 00:47:27,248
- It certainly is large.
- Yes.

1368
00:47:27,508 --> 00:47:28,918
It's really big.

1369
00:47:30,348 --> 00:47:31,748
It's good.

1370
00:47:33,218 --> 00:47:35,758
- It's spicy.
- It's delicious.

1371
00:47:36,218 --> 00:47:38,187
I bet a lot of people cure their hangovers with this.

1372
00:47:38,188 --> 00:47:40,487
Right. This alone could be...

1373
00:47:40,488 --> 00:47:42,697
- food for drinks.
- You're right.

1374
00:47:42,698 --> 00:47:44,327
- If they like to drink.
- With some soju.

1375
00:47:44,328 --> 00:47:46,328
(It's satisfying just to think about it.)

1376
00:47:46,368 --> 00:47:47,727
Young Dae, you like to drink, right?

1377
00:47:47,728 --> 00:47:49,097
I don't drink that often anymore.

1378
00:47:49,098 --> 00:47:50,397
- Not anymore.
- No?

1379
00:47:50,398 --> 00:47:52,468
- Why not?
- I just drank less often.

1380
00:47:52,568 --> 00:47:54,338
- That's good.
- Yes.

1381
00:47:54,708 --> 00:47:55,808
Well done, Young Dae.

1382
00:47:56,438 --> 00:47:58,307
- What about you, Sun Bin?
- I don't drink at all.

1383
00:47:58,308 --> 00:48:00,208
- You don't?
- Not at all.

1384
00:48:00,448 --> 00:48:02,518
Even when I turned 20, I never drank.

1385
00:48:02,748 --> 00:48:03,917
- You've never drunk?
- No.

1386
00:48:03,918 --> 00:48:05,347
- But...
- It doesn't suit you, then.

1387
00:48:05,348 --> 00:48:07,264
- It doesn't.
- But on "Work Later, Drink Now..."

1388
00:48:07,288 --> 00:48:08,818
Yes, it was a big fat lie.

1389
00:48:10,888 --> 00:48:15,558
(How did she act a heavy drinker so flawlessly, then?)

1390
00:48:15,698 --> 00:48:17,338
You mixed the drinks so well on the show.

1391
00:48:17,528 --> 00:48:20,367
I get to see how people get drunk...

1392
00:48:20,368 --> 00:48:22,167
- more clearly.
- I see.

1393
00:48:22,168 --> 00:48:24,768
- You get to observe them.
- Exactly.

1394
00:48:24,798 --> 00:48:25,868
I see.

1395
00:48:26,408 --> 00:48:29,007
She can't drink at all.

1396
00:48:29,008 --> 00:48:30,207
(Witness)

1397
00:48:30,208 --> 00:48:31,748
But she talks the most.

1398
00:48:32,048 --> 00:48:33,147
- At gatherings.
- She's the life of the party.

1399
00:48:33,148 --> 00:48:35,007
Yes. And she's the most energetic.

1400
00:48:35,008 --> 00:48:37,018
People think that I'm already drunk.

1401
00:48:37,178 --> 00:48:38,647
(Laughing)

1402
00:48:38,648 --> 00:48:41,618
So, it's an interesting feeling to me.

1403
00:48:41,958 --> 00:48:44,487
- When people see food, - They crave drinks.

1404
00:48:44,488 --> 00:48:46,057
They crave a certain drink.

1405
00:48:46,058 --> 00:48:48,087
- "This would go well with wine."
- Right.

1406
00:48:48,088 --> 00:48:51,497
I don't like the alcohol itself.

1407
00:48:51,498 --> 00:48:53,627
- When I eat the food...
- The combination?

1408
00:48:53,628 --> 00:48:54,797
Yes, the pair.

1409
00:48:54,798 --> 00:48:55,837
(Drinks and food have their own pairs.)

1410
00:48:55,838 --> 00:48:57,537
- It reminds me of the other.
- Yes.

1411
00:48:57,538 --> 00:48:58,968
It must be similar...

1412
00:48:59,138 --> 00:49:01,268
to craving donuts when you're drinking coffee.

1413
00:49:01,368 --> 00:49:02,878
It's something like that.

1414
00:49:03,308 --> 00:49:05,647
It's good, though.

1415
00:49:05,648 --> 00:49:07,447
It is. And it's filling.

1416
00:49:07,448 --> 00:49:08,648
- It really is filling.
- Yes.

1417
00:49:09,918 --> 00:49:11,018
- It's big.
- The best.

1418
00:49:12,388 --> 00:49:14,848
I finished a bowl of rice in an instant.

1419
00:49:15,358 --> 00:49:16,518
We have to decide who pays.

1420
00:49:16,958 --> 00:49:18,388
- We must.
- You're so...

1421
00:49:18,428 --> 00:49:20,357
I'm going to get an upset stomach.

1422
00:49:20,358 --> 00:49:22,127
The ones who were on this show said...

1423
00:49:22,128 --> 00:49:23,657
they had to bring their wallet.

1424
00:49:23,658 --> 00:49:24,997
- They must.
- Yes.

1425
00:49:24,998 --> 00:49:26,068
That's true.

1426
00:49:26,468 --> 00:49:27,968
How about pulling out glass noodles?

1427
00:49:28,638 --> 00:49:30,497
- The shortest one loses?
- Short or long?

1428
00:49:30,498 --> 00:49:32,007
- I like that.
- So, what's the rule?

1429
00:49:32,008 --> 00:49:33,607
- The short one...
- The shortest one loses.

1430
00:49:33,608 --> 00:49:34,867
- The shortest one loses.
- Okay?

1431
00:49:34,868 --> 00:49:35,877
The one who pulls the shortest one loses.

1432
00:49:35,878 --> 00:49:37,178
- Yes, the shortest one.
- Okay.

1433
00:49:37,908 --> 00:49:40,347
I'm sure he'll pull a short one on purpose.

1434
00:49:40,348 --> 00:49:41,508
He doesn't do that.

1435
00:49:41,948 --> 00:49:43,018
I don't do that.

1436
00:49:44,118 --> 00:49:45,247
Man.

1437
00:49:45,248 --> 00:49:46,547
(Jae Suk tries.)

1438
00:49:46,548 --> 00:49:48,017
But you can't pull the one that's sticking out.

1439
00:49:48,018 --> 00:49:49,557
Is this one all right?

1440
00:49:49,558 --> 00:49:51,057
- It's cut!
- It's cut.

1441
00:49:51,058 --> 00:49:52,557
- It's been cut. That's yours.
- No.

1442
00:49:52,558 --> 00:49:54,327
- No! It's this one.
- It's been cut.

1443
00:49:54,328 --> 00:49:55,527
- It's cut off.
- No.

1444
00:49:55,528 --> 00:49:58,128
This one.

1445
00:49:58,358 --> 00:50:00,127
- But you cut it.
- No, this is the one.

1446
00:50:00,128 --> 00:50:01,368
(It's not that short.)

1447
00:50:01,938 --> 00:50:02,997
I like how this one looks.

1448
00:50:02,998 --> 00:50:04,038
(Yeon Seok goes second.)

1449
00:50:04,498 --> 00:50:06,167
No, it's shorter than Jae Suk's.

1450
00:50:06,168 --> 00:50:07,237
- The longer, the better?
- Okay.

1451
00:50:07,238 --> 00:50:08,367
My noodle is slightly longer.

1452
00:50:08,368 --> 00:50:09,378
(Jae Suk wins by a hair.)

1453
00:50:09,778 --> 00:50:11,308
It might get cut off.

1454
00:50:12,048 --> 00:50:13,248
(Pulling)

1455
00:50:13,878 --> 00:50:15,077
Wait. Sun Bin.

1456
00:50:15,078 --> 00:50:18,418
- Hold on. No!
- You cut yours.

1457
00:50:18,848 --> 00:50:20,247
(She's forced to submit the short noodle.)

1458
00:50:20,248 --> 00:50:21,418
Now, Young Dae.

1459
00:50:22,018 --> 00:50:24,087
The way he uses his chopsticks makes it easy to cut.

1460
00:50:24,088 --> 00:50:25,557
Wait. It's short.

1461
00:50:25,558 --> 00:50:27,057
Is it shorter? It was cut.

1462
00:50:27,058 --> 00:50:29,027
- Was it?
- It just cut off.

1463
00:50:29,028 --> 00:50:30,958
- You two are similar.
- Hold up.

1464
00:50:31,358 --> 00:50:33,198
None of them is long.

1465
00:50:33,428 --> 00:50:35,437
It's Young Dae. It was cut off.

1466
00:50:35,438 --> 00:50:36,497
Thanks for the food!

1467
00:50:36,498 --> 00:50:38,038
Young Dae is unlucky.

1468
00:50:38,168 --> 00:50:39,507
- I didn't know it was cut off.
- I thought mine was long.

1469
00:50:39,508 --> 00:50:40,767
It was, though.

1470
00:50:40,768 --> 00:50:42,337
- Thanks for the food, Young Dae.
- I enjoyed the food.

1471
00:50:42,338 --> 00:50:44,678
It feels bad to have the youngest pay.

1472
00:50:44,778 --> 00:50:46,507
Having the youngest one of the group pay...

1473
00:50:46,508 --> 00:50:48,007
(Scoffing)

1474
00:50:48,008 --> 00:50:49,277
It's been so long.

1475
00:50:49,278 --> 00:50:51,638
Then, do you mind calling it a trial round and going again?

1476
00:50:52,218 --> 00:50:53,947
- We can't do that.
- No?

1477
00:50:53,948 --> 00:50:55,117
I'm afraid not.

1478
00:50:55,118 --> 00:50:57,917
Did you only say that to show pity?

1479
00:50:57,918 --> 00:50:59,658
- I just felt bad.
- You just felt bad.

1480
00:50:59,928 --> 00:51:01,488
- That's all.
- Okay.

1481
00:51:02,498 --> 00:51:03,598
I'm full.

1482
00:51:05,368 --> 00:51:07,328
- Can I go to the restroom?
- Sure.

1483
00:51:07,898 --> 00:51:08,997
You can go, Young Dae.

1484
00:51:08,998 --> 00:51:11,567
(Young Dae will go to the restroom.)

1485
00:51:11,568 --> 00:51:12,768
Man, I'm full.

1486
00:51:14,268 --> 00:51:15,877
- Isn't Young Dae cute, though?
- Yes.

1487
00:51:15,878 --> 00:51:18,608
He was so afraid of asking for permission to go to the restroom.

1488
00:51:19,448 --> 00:51:20,477
He was also born in the Year of the Mouse.

1489
00:51:20,478 --> 00:51:21,508
Really?

1490
00:51:22,248 --> 00:51:24,168
- Young Dae...
- So there are three cycles here?

1491
00:51:25,688 --> 00:51:27,368
He was also born in the Year of the Mouse.

1492
00:51:27,748 --> 00:51:29,117
- Are you serious?
- He's...

1493
00:51:29,118 --> 00:51:30,517
You're all 12 years apart?

1494
00:51:30,518 --> 00:51:31,518
(Born in 1984, born in 1972, and born in 1996)

1495
00:51:31,519 --> 00:51:32,527
(The Year of the Mouse Trio)

1496
00:51:32,528 --> 00:51:33,834
- That's insane.
- Three whole cycles.

1497
00:51:33,858 --> 00:51:36,397
And we made the youngest one pay.

1498
00:51:36,398 --> 00:51:38,927
(The older mice got free food from the youngest mouse.)

1499
00:51:38,928 --> 00:51:40,127
Then, Young Dae...

1500
00:51:40,128 --> 00:51:41,398
He couldn't have bolted, right?

1501
00:51:42,768 --> 00:51:44,198
- This kid.
- No, right?

1502
00:51:44,438 --> 00:51:46,437
- Here he is.
- I forgot to pay.

1503
00:51:46,438 --> 00:51:48,267
- You have to pay.
- Young Dae.

1504
00:51:48,268 --> 00:51:49,907
- We've been waiting for you.
- We have.

1505
00:51:49,908 --> 00:51:51,838
- Your wallet is here, right?
- Yes, it is.

1506
00:51:52,448 --> 00:51:54,907
Don't tell me you forgot your wallet.

1507
00:51:54,908 --> 00:51:56,177
(They're busy teasing the youngest mouse.)

1508
00:51:56,178 --> 00:51:57,318
I have it.

1509
00:51:57,918 --> 00:51:59,687
- Thanks for the food. Yes.
- Did you enjoy it?

1510
00:51:59,688 --> 00:52:00,918
(It's on the youngest mouse.)

1511
00:52:01,518 --> 00:52:04,457
It's rare to get free food from the youngest one...

1512
00:52:04,458 --> 00:52:05,727
born in the Year of the Mouse.

1513
00:52:05,728 --> 00:52:07,457
- I had no idea.
- Right.

1514
00:52:07,458 --> 00:52:10,627
I wouldn't have let him pay if I had known.

1515
00:52:10,628 --> 00:52:11,734
(Murmuring empty words as he's embarrassed)

1516
00:52:11,758 --> 00:52:13,267
Thanks for the food, Young Dae.

1517
00:52:13,268 --> 00:52:14,727
(Checking the receipt)

1518
00:52:14,728 --> 00:52:16,237
That must have cost a bit. You're checking the receipt.

1519
00:52:16,238 --> 00:52:18,198
Young Dae, you've always been eating lunch alone.

1520
00:52:19,368 --> 00:52:21,707
And it's surprising to see such a big check, isn't it?

1521
00:52:21,708 --> 00:52:22,708
- Yes, a little.
- Let me see.

1522
00:52:22,709 --> 00:52:24,107
- He said, "Yes, a little."
- Gosh.

1523
00:52:24,108 --> 00:52:25,278
It was 880 dollars.

1524
00:52:26,008 --> 00:52:28,007
I feel good about the number. It was 88 dollars.

1525
00:52:28,008 --> 00:52:29,377
- Eighty-eight.
- Eighty-eight.

1526
00:52:29,378 --> 00:52:30,577
I heard you were born in the Year of the Mouse.

1527
00:52:30,578 --> 00:52:31,578
I was.

1528
00:52:31,618 --> 00:52:32,787
- So were we.
- Hey.

1529
00:52:32,788 --> 00:52:34,317
- So were we.
- Seriously?

1530
00:52:34,318 --> 00:52:36,017
We were both born in the Year of the Mouse.

1531
00:52:36,018 --> 00:52:37,717
- First, second...
- He's the oldest mouse.

1532
00:52:37,718 --> 00:52:38,887
- Yes.
- I'm the youngest mouse, then.

1533
00:52:38,888 --> 00:52:39,987
- Yes!
- You are.

1534
00:52:39,988 --> 00:52:41,187
Three generations in one place.

1535
00:52:41,188 --> 00:52:43,527
- We're the mouse trio.
- We're all mice.

1536
00:52:43,528 --> 00:52:44,634
(It happened to be a group of 3 mice.)

1537
00:52:44,658 --> 00:52:46,998
- We're all mice.
- Let's get going.

1538
00:52:48,068 --> 00:52:49,868
I got free food from the youngest mouse.

1539
00:52:50,198 --> 00:52:52,468
It feels good to get free food from the youngest mouse.

1540
00:52:52,938 --> 00:52:54,107
I feel great.

1541
00:52:54,108 --> 00:52:55,238
That was a great meal.

1542
00:52:56,608 --> 00:53:00,407
The first-generation mouse will buy coffee for us.

1543
00:53:00,408 --> 00:53:02,048
- We turn right here.
- Turn right?

1544
00:53:02,848 --> 00:53:04,118
This area...

1545
00:53:04,748 --> 00:53:07,187
has lots of cute shops.

1546
00:53:07,188 --> 00:53:09,017
You're right. It's nice and cute.

1547
00:53:09,018 --> 00:53:10,088
It is.

1548
00:53:10,358 --> 00:53:12,757
- The alley...
- It looks pretty hip.

1549
00:53:12,758 --> 00:53:14,288
- Why is it so...
- Here.

1550
00:53:15,898 --> 00:53:17,327
- Let's check it out.
- Sure.

1551
00:53:17,328 --> 00:53:18,427
It looked beautiful.

1552
00:53:18,428 --> 00:53:19,468
- Did it?
- Yes.

1553
00:53:19,728 --> 00:53:20,998
This place is...

1554
00:53:21,398 --> 00:53:23,097
It's a quiet coffee shop.

1555
00:53:23,098 --> 00:53:24,338
Oh, my. It is.

1556
00:53:24,398 --> 00:53:25,867
Hello.

1557
00:53:25,868 --> 00:53:28,208
- Hello.
- Hello.

1558
00:53:28,468 --> 00:53:30,477
- It's beautiful.
- It's cozy.

1559
00:53:30,478 --> 00:53:32,648
- It's a warm vibe.
- Yes.

1560
00:53:33,308 --> 00:53:34,748
- It's a teahouse.
- Yes.

1561
00:53:34,908 --> 00:53:36,148
They have milk tea.

1562
00:53:36,478 --> 00:53:37,917
They also have grilled bar rice cakes.

1563
00:53:37,918 --> 00:53:39,248
Right. We should try that.

1564
00:53:39,318 --> 00:53:40,388
And cookies.

1565
00:53:40,548 --> 00:53:43,187
We'll have a grain cookie and a bar rice cake.

1566
00:53:43,188 --> 00:53:45,588
Sure thing. We have two types of cookies.

1567
00:53:46,328 --> 00:53:47,658
Which one is more popular?

1568
00:53:47,858 --> 00:53:49,697
- We'll take both.
- Sure.

1569
00:53:49,698 --> 00:53:50,998
- Nice.
- Good choice.

1570
00:53:51,428 --> 00:53:52,428
You're flexing.

1571
00:53:52,928 --> 00:53:54,098
It's on Jae Suk, so...

1572
00:53:54,768 --> 00:53:55,867
Yeon Seok.

1573
00:53:55,868 --> 00:53:57,067
(Let's feast since Jae Suk is buying.)

1574
00:53:57,068 --> 00:53:59,007
Can I get cold tea instead of warm tea?

1575
00:53:59,008 --> 00:54:00,008
Of course.

1576
00:54:00,009 --> 00:54:01,307
I'll have a cold one, then.

1577
00:54:01,308 --> 00:54:02,577
Which one?

1578
00:54:02,578 --> 00:54:04,008
He must be...

1579
00:54:04,108 --> 00:54:05,978
seething inside from paying for lunch.

1580
00:54:07,248 --> 00:54:09,018
- Iced tea.
- Iced tea.

1581
00:54:09,118 --> 00:54:10,147
Thanks.

1582
00:54:10,148 --> 00:54:11,447
Thank you.

1583
00:54:11,448 --> 00:54:12,987
It's only half...

1584
00:54:12,988 --> 00:54:16,318
compared to what Young Dae had to pay.

1585
00:54:16,618 --> 00:54:18,217
I love this atmosphere.

1586
00:54:18,218 --> 00:54:20,088
- I know, right?
- It's warm.

1587
00:54:20,458 --> 00:54:21,987
You're still wearing your gloves.

1588
00:54:21,988 --> 00:54:23,957
Give this to Sun Bin.

1589
00:54:23,958 --> 00:54:25,898
- Sun Bin. Here.
- Me?

1590
00:54:26,298 --> 00:54:29,637
- Take it.
- Thank you.

1591
00:54:29,638 --> 00:54:31,467
- Good. Sun Bin, - Well done.

1592
00:54:31,468 --> 00:54:33,967
Stay warm. Let's use it together.

1593
00:54:33,968 --> 00:54:35,307
Sure.

1594
00:54:35,308 --> 00:54:37,538
Why are you using it together?

1595
00:54:37,578 --> 00:54:39,047
Yeon Seok's coat is...

1596
00:54:39,048 --> 00:54:40,077
(Yeon Seok's coat is the best when it's cold.)

1597
00:54:40,078 --> 00:54:42,078
- Use it. It's cold.
- That's so funny.

1598
00:54:43,118 --> 00:54:44,347
- Oh, here it is.
- Thank you.

1599
00:54:44,348 --> 00:54:46,648
- Thank you.
- It's so cute!

1600
00:54:46,788 --> 00:54:47,948
These are the bar rice cakes.

1601
00:54:50,318 --> 00:54:51,387
It's good.

1602
00:54:51,388 --> 00:54:53,387
- The honey isn't too sweet.
- No. I like it.

1603
00:54:53,388 --> 00:54:54,388
(Moaning)

1604
00:54:54,788 --> 00:54:57,557
I like the vibe of a teahouse.

1605
00:54:57,558 --> 00:54:58,558
(Slurping the warm mixed grain drink)

1606
00:54:58,559 --> 00:54:59,998
- It's really good.
- It is.

1607
00:55:01,528 --> 00:55:02,567
(Young Dae also takes a big bite.)

1608
00:55:02,568 --> 00:55:03,898
- It's good.
- How does it taste?

1609
00:55:05,298 --> 00:55:06,567
I've never seen you...

1610
00:55:06,568 --> 00:55:08,407
eat this well until today.

1611
00:55:08,408 --> 00:55:09,478
Is he a small eater?

1612
00:55:09,878 --> 00:55:12,147
I'm not, but I rarely eat during a shoot.

1613
00:55:12,148 --> 00:55:13,848
Oh, this is also a shoot.

1614
00:55:14,348 --> 00:55:16,577
- When I'm filming dramas, - Yes.

1615
00:55:16,578 --> 00:55:18,848
- You can't digest well?
- if I eat too much...

1616
00:55:19,148 --> 00:55:20,748
- Because you feel too full?
- Yes.

1617
00:55:21,218 --> 00:55:22,557
Do you prefer filling your belly before a shoot?

1618
00:55:22,558 --> 00:55:24,918
Yes. I even eat during the shoot.

1619
00:55:25,418 --> 00:55:27,258
- You try to fill your belly.
- Yes.

1620
00:55:27,558 --> 00:55:30,128
I eat just enough to keep the hunger away.

1621
00:55:30,398 --> 00:55:32,028
Before important scenes, I mean.

1622
00:55:32,468 --> 00:55:34,927
Weirdly enough, I can't get into character when I'm full.

1623
00:55:34,928 --> 00:55:36,567
- Really?
- Yes. Maybe it's just me.

1624
00:55:36,568 --> 00:55:39,668
- You're right.
- But when I'm hungry,

1625
00:55:39,838 --> 00:55:41,808
it's easier to feel sad.

1626
00:55:42,878 --> 00:55:45,137
(Taking a bite to fight the sadness off)

1627
00:55:45,138 --> 00:55:47,177
Young Dae, you started out as a model, didn't you?

1628
00:55:47,178 --> 00:55:49,877
Yes, I didn't have any skills at first,

1629
00:55:49,878 --> 00:55:51,947
- so I did modeling jobs...
- Really?

1630
00:55:51,948 --> 00:55:53,148
While learning how to act.

1631
00:55:53,748 --> 00:55:55,347
That's interesting. I had no idea.

1632
00:55:55,348 --> 00:55:56,787
Kwang Soo also used to be a model.

1633
00:55:56,788 --> 00:55:57,788
I know.

1634
00:55:57,818 --> 00:55:58,987
I was surprised.

1635
00:55:58,988 --> 00:56:00,488
Kwang Soo used to be a model.

1636
00:56:00,558 --> 00:56:02,198
- Kwang Soo...
- Right.

1637
00:56:02,528 --> 00:56:04,098
- We met.
- I met him yesterday.

1638
00:56:04,158 --> 00:56:05,197
- You met him yesterday?
- Really?

1639
00:56:05,198 --> 00:56:06,968
Yes. It was hilarious.

1640
00:56:06,998 --> 00:56:08,027
Was it your first time?

1641
00:56:08,028 --> 00:56:09,998
He tried to tell me nice things.

1642
00:56:10,698 --> 00:56:13,238
He sat me down and said some serious stuff.

1643
00:56:13,768 --> 00:56:15,338
I was such a big fan...

1644
00:56:15,438 --> 00:56:17,377
that every time I looked at him...

1645
00:56:17,378 --> 00:56:19,547
- You laughed.
- I shouldn't, but I...

1646
00:56:19,548 --> 00:56:20,647
couldn't help it when he was talking seriously.

1647
00:56:20,648 --> 00:56:22,317
- Like, "Say hi to people."
- "You need to say hi to people."

1648
00:56:22,318 --> 00:56:24,554
- He told him to be kind.
- "Work hard while you still can."

1649
00:56:24,578 --> 00:56:26,717
And my lips twitched without realizing.

1650
00:56:26,718 --> 00:56:29,017
While he was speaking so seriously.

1651
00:56:29,018 --> 00:56:30,118
And he said,

1652
00:56:30,418 --> 00:56:32,488
"Did you just laugh?"

1653
00:56:32,558 --> 00:56:34,887
And that was also funny, so I laughed again.

1654
00:56:34,888 --> 00:56:36,357
He knows when to say...

1655
00:56:36,358 --> 00:56:37,797
- what's funny.
- Yes.

1656
00:56:37,798 --> 00:56:39,298
Even when you went to the bathroom,

1657
00:56:39,428 --> 00:56:41,067
- he told you to get permission.
- He said, "Did you get permission?"

1658
00:56:41,068 --> 00:56:42,798
He scolded Young Dae continuously.

1659
00:56:43,468 --> 00:56:45,468
- Didn't he learn that from you?
- It was from me.

1660
00:56:47,108 --> 00:56:48,468
I taught him everything.

1661
00:56:48,908 --> 00:56:50,838
I laughed all day.

1662
00:56:51,308 --> 00:56:53,878
How far is our next destination?

1663
00:56:53,948 --> 00:56:55,847
- It's less than five minutes.
- Really?

1664
00:56:55,848 --> 00:56:57,148
- Five minutes?
- Really?

1665
00:56:57,718 --> 00:56:59,788
Kim Hyun Seung and Kim Ye Seung.

1666
00:57:00,488 --> 00:57:01,917
"Even when it's cold,"

1667
00:57:01,918 --> 00:57:04,387
"we train from Tuesday to Sunday."

1668
00:57:04,388 --> 00:57:05,417
- What?
- "Train?"

1669
00:57:05,418 --> 00:57:07,058
They train every day except for Monday.

1670
00:57:07,328 --> 00:57:09,998
"Our goal is to become famous."

1671
00:57:10,098 --> 00:57:12,728
"That way, we get newbies and go to competitions."

1672
00:57:12,798 --> 00:57:15,667
"And we're going to be superstars in the future,"

1673
00:57:15,668 --> 00:57:18,938
"so we want to remember how we are now."

1674
00:57:19,838 --> 00:57:21,108
Are they athletes?

1675
00:57:21,268 --> 00:57:22,277
- They could be...
- Baseball?

1676
00:57:22,278 --> 00:57:23,307
Like an athletic club.

1677
00:57:23,308 --> 00:57:24,584
(Are they visiting an athletic club next?)

1678
00:57:24,608 --> 00:57:28,247
If we're going to an elementary school...

1679
00:57:28,248 --> 00:57:31,048
and they're elementary school students...

1680
00:57:31,918 --> 00:57:32,948
(Sighing)

1681
00:57:33,248 --> 00:57:34,688
- It's a lot of pressure.
- Yes.

1682
00:57:35,048 --> 00:57:37,128
I have the intelligence of an elementary school kid,

1683
00:57:37,218 --> 00:57:38,658
so I can meet them at eye level.

1684
00:57:39,388 --> 00:57:41,357
- I can get along with them.
- Good.

1685
00:57:41,358 --> 00:57:42,857
- All right, Young Dae.
- Yes.

1686
00:57:42,858 --> 00:57:43,997
- We'll trust you.
- Sure.

1687
00:57:43,998 --> 00:57:45,704
(We'll trust Young Dae and visit the next guests.)

1688
00:57:45,728 --> 00:57:46,768
What time is it?

1689
00:57:46,828 --> 00:57:48,297
Shall we get going?

1690
00:57:48,298 --> 00:57:49,337
- Thank you for the coffee.
- Thank you.

1691
00:57:49,338 --> 00:57:50,498
- Goodbye.
- Thank you.

1692
00:57:51,098 --> 00:57:53,367
We're on our way to meet future superstars.

1693
00:57:53,368 --> 00:57:54,407
Yes.

1694
00:57:54,408 --> 00:57:55,754
("And we're going to be superstars in the future.")

1695
00:57:55,778 --> 00:57:57,108
I should befriend them now.

1696
00:58:01,378 --> 00:58:03,148
(Turning)

1697
00:58:03,318 --> 00:58:04,647
I feel like it's a school.

1698
00:58:04,648 --> 00:58:05,748
- Yes.
- I think so too.

1699
00:58:05,848 --> 00:58:06,887
(They see an elementary school.)

1700
00:58:06,888 --> 00:58:08,818
That's the one. "Elementary School."

1701
00:58:09,418 --> 00:58:11,457
- Is that it?
- That must be it.

1702
00:58:11,458 --> 00:58:13,258
- It was right nearby.
- Is that the one?

1703
00:58:14,158 --> 00:58:15,327
(They follow the address and arrive at Inhun Elementary.)

1704
00:58:15,328 --> 00:58:17,958
I bet a lot of them are late for school while walking up here.

1705
00:58:18,698 --> 00:58:19,728
Jeez.

1706
00:58:20,468 --> 00:58:22,197
(A long climb up the steep hill...)

1707
00:58:22,198 --> 00:58:23,867
- Wait.
- What's Inhun Growing Site?

1708
00:58:23,868 --> 00:58:24,937
This is it.

1709
00:58:24,938 --> 00:58:26,218
- It's right here.
- Right here.

1710
00:58:27,068 --> 00:58:28,467
- It's right here.
- It is.

1711
00:58:28,468 --> 00:58:29,678
Inhun Growing Site?

1712
00:58:29,938 --> 00:58:31,138
What's this?

1713
00:58:31,308 --> 00:58:32,648
Isn't this a kindergarten?

1714
00:58:34,078 --> 00:58:35,107
It can't be, right?

1715
00:58:35,108 --> 00:58:36,647
(There's a future superstar here?)

1716
00:58:36,648 --> 00:58:38,317
- What is it?
- I think it's a gym.

1717
00:58:38,318 --> 00:58:39,687
- A gym.
- Is it baseball?

1718
00:58:39,688 --> 00:58:41,048
Are they baseball players?

1719
00:58:41,318 --> 00:58:43,058
- It's baseball!
- Baseball.

1720
00:58:43,118 --> 00:58:44,157
It was baseball.

1721
00:58:44,158 --> 00:58:45,558
(Through the crack in the door, )

1722
00:58:45,618 --> 00:58:48,128
(they see little baseball players.)

1723
00:58:48,358 --> 00:58:51,227
(They're busy practicing.)

1724
00:58:51,228 --> 00:58:54,498
- What were their names?
- Kim Hyun Seung and Kim Ye Seung.

1725
00:58:54,598 --> 00:58:55,838
Hello.

1726
00:58:56,068 --> 00:58:57,597
- Hello.
- Hello.

1727
00:58:57,598 --> 00:58:59,438
(Taking their hats off)

1728
00:58:59,808 --> 00:59:02,437
- Look at them.
- They take their hats off too.

1729
00:59:02,438 --> 00:59:03,478
I know.

1730
00:59:04,438 --> 00:59:06,107
(When he says hello the second time, )

1731
00:59:06,108 --> 00:59:08,407
(they take their hats off and bow.)

1732
00:59:08,408 --> 00:59:09,678
They're disciplined.

1733
00:59:09,718 --> 00:59:11,748
